In one of the threads on there - can't remember which board and what the thread it pertained to - people started getting on to very depressing topics. Didn't help that I was already very depressed, mostly brought on by the decrepit state of the world at the time. I felt like shit, and was really asking what the point of it all was. I had taken the black pill in full force. Then some kind anon in the thread convinced me and got me out of my bout of depression, and to this day, I remain faithful, optimistic, and most importantly, resolute in my purpose. You know what he said?

>If you kill yourself, the Jews win.

posts.subject: Return of Gamenight: No Semitics Edition
posts.body:
I think this board could use some more unity. There's no better a way of doing that than getting a gamenight started. Since the board is so slow, I think it would be beneficial to schedule this out a week or two (or three) in advance. 

Let's get a list going for things we'll need to iron out before the actual game night.

1. What game will we be playing?
2. When?
3. Who will host? 

I'll put a few names out for possible games, but go ahead and suggest your own ideas. Just keep in mind that the smaller and easier to access, the better. Nobody really wants to download 10's of gigs and go through hoops to play a multiplayer game for one night. 

I know that hosts are in short supply, but a backup host for every primary host is worth  the effort. Or, depending on the game, an existing dedicated server - preferably free of normalfags - will suffice. 

Possible games: 
>Team Fortress Classic
>Star Wars Battlefront (not EA shit)
>Dawn of War
>Killing Floor (1)
>Day of Defeat (Goldsrc)
>CS 1.6
>Serious Sam
>Left 4 Dead Versus

>>e02bdd41-21c1-4620-883f-b379c331ace5
What the fuck do you mean that 6 and 7 and 8 are mediocre? The GBA fire emblem games are golden. Babby's first Fire Emblem is the DS and 3DS shit (with the exception of Echoes). 
>fun ones
I hope you're not referring to 4 or 5, those two definitely aren't fun at all, and I wish I could get back the time I spent playing all of that. I also don't think the gamecube games are very fun, either. Radiant Dawn even has a section where you NEED to have the foresight to bring a hammer or some anti-armor weapon and give it to Ike or else you ''will not'' win and are forced to go back three levels (provided you have a saved spot in the first place).

>>c8acfdca-b96a-4ec8-8071-80caccbcf817
>they aren't made for people who don't use their tools to the fullest
What does this even mean? Are you referring to inheritances? Because that's also bullshit. Unless you're familiar with the game beforehand or have read a strategy book or watched some youtube videos explaining it, you could go through the entire game and be unaware of how the inheritances really work, and even then, it's almost complete guesswork as to how the legendary weapons are obtained. Not to mention how the recruitment for some characters are absolutely pants-on-head retarded, so you would be quite literally clueless with certain characters. 

I'll use an example. Did any of you realize how to recruit Arya? You had to completely pass by her with Sigurd, go to the castle, then go all the way back to talk to her with Sigurd. All while Arya is attacking one of your own units, and unless you had the luck of the gods, you wouldn't have recruited her without losing a unit, let alone figure out the process at all. 

Oh, and dare we forget the forced unit death level? Not talking about when Sigurd and co. dies. The one that comes afterwards.
